MEMBERSHIP PROGRAMS
Experience the best of golf with an Indian River golf membership. Enjoy fun rounds, exceptional service, and our stunning course surrounded by nature. Tee off to memorable moments – join us today!
Membership benefits include:
Unlimited golf and carts
Unlimited range and practice facility access
Up to 10% off full-price merchandise
10% off at Andrei’s
Annual Membership
MEMBERSHIP RATES
$3600 Single | $5500 Couple
RESIDENT RATES
$3300 Single | $5100 Couple
Seasonal Membership
SEASONAL MEMBERSHIP RATES
$400 Per Month For Single (three month minimum)
$650 Per Month For Couple (three month minimum)
Other Golf Program Options
Indian River Preserve Winter Player’s Card: November – April | $89
Indian River Preserve Summer Player’s Card: May – October | $69
Benefits:
Play for free on the day you sign up!
Reduced rates for daily tee times
Morning $10 discount
Afternoon $5 discount
Complimentary small bucket of balls prior to your tee times
25% off coupon at Andrei’s
Range Membership
$400 annually
$40 monthly (three minimum months)
Unlimited range and $27 golf after 2 p.m.
IRP Residents Card
Welcome IRP Residents! Did you know residents of our community receive a $5 discount on every greens free?
To learn more and register for programs and memberships, contact Marsha Gault, Director of Sales and Marketing, Marsha.Gault@bobbyjoneslinks.com or (321) 385-2099.
All programs and Membership require appropriate application and management approval. Eligibility requirements must be met including proof of residency. Pricing and discounts are subject to change. Cards and memberships are non-transferable and non-refundable. See the club for full details and registration information.

About Us
Originally opened in 2003, Indian River Preserve Golf Club is an 18-hole golf course, co-designed by renowned golf course architect Perry Dye and LPGA champion Jan Stephenson. The course features lush fairways across a rolling landscape, surrounded by serene lakes, nature preserves, and wildlife. Indian River Preserve is home to Andrei’s Restaurant serving chef-driven menus to the public.
